en_7057283_0	A three-month amnesty period has been granted to navy personnel who left service without following  proper procedure, to report back to work.
en_7057283_1	Navy Spokesperson Commander Indika de Silva said that these personnel can call on the nearest navy base and report to work.
en_7057283_2	He added that these individuals will be given an opportunity to leave the navy legally on the same day that they report to work.
en_7057283_3	The navy spokesperson noted that those personnel who are enrolled in various courses and those who have signed agreements with the navy will not be allowed to leave until they complete their due time.
